== Personal life ==
In 1963, Cocker began dating Eileen Webster, also a resident of Sheffield. The couple dated intermittently for the next 13 years, and separated permanently in 1976.{{sfn|Bean|2003|p=15}}<ref>{{Cite web|title=Joe Cocker|url=https://en.24smi.org/celebrity/55167-joe-cocker.html|access-date=2021-01-11|website=en.24smi.org|language=en}}</ref>

In 1978, Cocker moved onto a ranch owned by [[Jane Fonda]] in [[Santa Barbara, California]]. Pam Baker, a local summer camp director and fan of Cocker's music, persuaded the actress to lend the house to Cocker. Baker began dating Cocker, and they married on 11 October 1987.{{sfn|Bean|2003|p=171}} The couple resided on the Mad Dog Ranch in Crawford, Colorado. 

While performing a concert at [[Madison Square Garden]] on 17 September 2014, fellow pop musician [[Billy Joel]] stated that Cocker was "not very well right now" and endorsed Cocker for induction into the [[Rock and Roll Hall of Fame]] before his tribute performance of "With a Little Help From My Friends".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://ultimateclassicrock.com/joe-cocker-health/| title=Billy Joel Says Joe Cocker Is 'Not Very Well Right Now'|first=Jeff|last=Giles|publisher=Ulimate Rock Classic.com|date=25 September 2014|access-date=31 October 2014}}</ref> Cocker died from [[lung cancer]] on 22 December 2014 in [[Crawford, Colorado]], at the age of 70.<ref name="Indep23dec14">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/news/joe-cocker-formidable-vocalist-who-triumphed-at-woodstock-and-won-a-grammy-with-up-where-we-belong-9943221.html |archive-url=https://ghostarchive.org/archive/20220609/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/news/joe-cocker-formidable-vocalist-who-triumphed-at-woodstock-and-won-a-grammy-with-up-where-we-belong-9943221.html |archive-date=9 June 2022 |url-access=subscription |url-status=live|title=Joe Cocker: Formidable vocalist who triumphed at Woodstock and won a Grammy with 'Up Where We Belong'|work=The Independent|date=23 December 2014|access-date=24 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/news/calendar/story/2014-12-22/joe-cocker-dies-aged-70/|title=Joe Cocker dies aged 70|work=ITV News|access-date=22 December 2014|date=22 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.wlox.com/story/27687382/musician-joe-cocker-dies-at-age-70 |title=Musician Joe Cocker dies at age 70 |publisher=WLOX |date=22 December 2014 |access-date=22 December 2014 |first=Matt |last=Quillen |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141222204927/http://www.wlox.com/story/27687382/musician-joe-cocker-dies-at-age-70 |archive-date=22 December 2014 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He had smoked 40 cigarettes a day until he quit in 1991.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.sun-sentinel.com/2000-10-17/news/0010160490_1_joe-camel-smoking-joe-cocker|title=Time And Trials Refine The Song Of Joe Cocker|website=Articles.sun-sentinel.com|access-date=25 January 2018}}</ref> Cocker is buried in the town cemetery in Crawford, Colorado.

